1
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:13,751
♫ Through the crowded, bustling streets ♫

2
00:00:13,751 --> 00:00:17,626
♫ Who will I say goodnight to? ♫

3
00:00:17,626 --> 00:00:19,999
♫ The vulnerability I long to embrace ♫

4
00:00:19,999 --> 00:00:22,918
♫ Is buried deep inside ♫

5
00:00:22,918 --> 00:00:26,584
♫ Under the moon's radiant glow, dreams surge and swell ♫

6
00:00:26,584 --> 00:00:28,999
♫ Waiting for a reason to run wild ♫

7
00:00:28,999 --> 00:00:36,125
♫ Can you walk with me for a while without saying a word? ♫

8
00:00:36,125 --> 00:00:39,167
♫ Follow the neon lights into the night ♫

9
00:00:39,167 --> 00:00:42,292
♫ I try to find you every night ♫

10
00:00:42,292 --> 00:00:47,125
♫ What must I do to see through that distant line? ♫

11
00:00:47,125 --> 00:00:52,042
♫ I want to feel the wind full force ♫

12
00:00:52,042 --> 00:00:55,167
♫ My lonely soul begins to shake ♫

13
00:00:55,167 --> 00:01:00,167
♫ What can we trust to forever endure? ♫

14
00:01:00,167 --> 00:01:04,999
♫ I want to bring my freedom forth, and take your hand ♫

15
00:01:04,999 --> 00:01:10,375
♫ When the warmth finally seeps into every memory's corner ♫

16
00:01:10,375 --> 00:01:18,799
♫ The past was never wrong, having us is enough forever ♫

17
00:01:26,792 --> 00:01:30,799
[Breeze by the Sea]

18
00:01:34,476 --> 00:01:37,685
You always feel unwell around this time of year.

19
00:01:37,685 --> 00:01:40,292
As we get older, falling is our worst fear.

20
00:01:40,292 --> 00:01:43,300
A single misstep can lead to long-term issues.

21
00:01:44,083 --> 00:01:46,619
Hasn't Da Wu already returned?

22
00:01:46,619 --> 00:01:49,375
Why do you still come here to see a doctor?

23
00:01:49,375 --> 00:01:51,375
It's all his fault.

24
00:01:51,375 --> 00:01:54,967
How childish. You fell on your own.

25
00:01:57,042 --> 00:01:59,918
Can you make me another pink one?

26
00:01:59,918 --> 00:02:01,799
Sure.

27
00:02:04,876 --> 00:02:07,042
Xu Man painted really well.

28
00:02:07,042 --> 00:02:09,786
Why don't you let her paint the whole car?

29
00:02:09,786 --> 00:02:14,726
Well, she said she saved the front for you

30
00:02:14,726 --> 00:02:16,800
since it's the most important part.

31
00:02:23,042 --> 00:02:26,799
Is your medical car really on call all the time?

32
00:02:27,999 --> 00:02:29,209
Hopefully not.

33
00:02:29,209 --> 00:02:32,125
I want everyone to stay healthy.

34
00:02:32,125 --> 00:02:34,250
I'd rather this car be ready but not needed.

35
00:02:34,250 --> 00:02:36,175
You're right.

36
00:02:38,794 --> 00:02:42,592
Then why did you ask me to paint a horseshoe crab on the front?

37
00:02:47,753 --> 00:02:49,759
Because...

38
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:56,999
It's cute.

39
00:02:56,999 --> 00:02:58,967
It's cute?

40
00:02:59,966 --> 00:03:02,799
What's so funny? Why are you smiling like that?

41
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:06,050
Shu Man.

42
00:03:07,294 --> 00:03:09,134
Shu Man.

43
00:03:10,436 --> 00:03:12,269
Hey, Mr. Bai.

44
00:03:12,269 --> 00:03:13,720
This fish is for...

45
00:03:13,720 --> 00:03:15,799
Just put it in the fridge.

46
00:03:31,867 --> 00:03:33,867
Shu Man is too kind.

47
00:03:33,867 --> 00:03:35,678
She probably didn't mention it to you,

48
00:03:35,678 --> 00:03:38,368
but they'll be very busy tomorrow.

49
00:03:38,368 --> 00:03:43,134
If possible, leave early and return late.

50
00:03:55,077 --> 00:03:57,669
If my dad were still around,

51
00:03:57,669 --> 00:04:01,621
he'd be thrilled to see

52
00:04:01,621 --> 00:04:03,676
his beloved car turned so cute.

53
00:04:04,786 --> 00:04:08,759
Yes, he'd definitely show it off to my dad.

54
00:04:10,735 --> 00:04:14,143
He'd even drive the car and take our moms

55
00:04:14,143 --> 00:04:17,893
to Sinda Temple to join the square dancing.

56
00:04:17,893 --> 00:04:19,083
Right.

57
00:04:19,083 --> 00:04:20,883
Square dancing.

58
00:04:21,610 --> 00:04:25,883
He'd also take your whole family on trips everywhere.

59
00:04:30,509 --> 00:04:32,867
Thank you, Da Wu.

60
00:04:32,867 --> 00:04:36,667
Thank you for giving this car

61
00:04:36,667 --> 00:04:39,959
a new life and a new journey.

62
00:04:39,959 --> 00:04:41,799
No need to thank me.

63
00:04:43,702 --> 00:04:46,660
Nuo Nuo, do you know where we're going later?

64
00:04:46,660 --> 00:04:47,687
I don't.

65
00:04:47,687 --> 00:04:50,292
We're taking you to see your favorite deer.

66
00:04:50,292 --> 00:04:51,751
I want to feed the deer.

67
00:04:51,751 --> 00:04:52,768
Of course you can.

68
00:04:52,768 --> 00:04:53,999
Aren't you afraid of getting bitten?

69
00:04:53,999 --> 00:04:56,334
I'm not afraid. I want to feed the deer.

70
00:04:56,334 --> 00:04:59,285
All right, but be careful and gentle.

71
00:04:59,285 --> 00:05:01,471
- Don't scare them, okay?
- Okay.

72
00:05:01,471 --> 00:05:04,667
Go slowly. Don't scare them.

73
00:05:04,667 --> 00:05:05,695
They're waiting for you.

74
00:05:05,695 --> 00:05:07,068
- Nuo Nuo.
- Yes.

75
00:05:07,068 --> 00:05:08,984
Bambi, do you want more?

76
00:05:08,984 --> 00:05:10,560
This one is called Bambi.

77
00:05:10,560 --> 00:05:12,334
Do you have a name?

78
00:05:12,334 --> 00:05:14,799
Little Bambi.

79
00:05:37,942 --> 00:05:39,967
Little Bambi.

80
00:05:43,669 --> 00:05:45,592
It has been a while.

81
00:05:46,794 --> 00:05:48,676
Little Bambi.

82
00:05:55,494 --> 00:05:57,669
Mr. Bai, you're still up.

83
00:05:57,669 --> 00:05:58,900
Yes.

84
00:05:58,900 --> 00:06:00,083
Right.

85
00:06:00,083 --> 00:06:01,568
An old lady brought a fish today.

86
00:06:01,568 --> 00:06:03,419
I told her to put it in the fridge.

87
00:06:03,419 --> 00:06:05,235
Do you mean Xiu E?

88
00:06:05,235 --> 00:06:06,436
I guess so.

89
00:06:06,436 --> 00:06:08,799
Okay, got it. Thank you.

90
00:06:09,584 --> 00:06:11,175
By the way...

91
00:06:13,834 --> 00:06:17,636
I'll probably be out early and back late tomorrow.

92
00:06:17,636 --> 00:06:21,478
So, you don't need to prepare any meals for me tomorrow.

93
00:06:21,478 --> 00:06:23,685
Did Xiu E tell you something?

94
00:06:23,685 --> 00:06:25,626
No, she didn't say anything.

95
00:06:25,626 --> 00:06:26,999
I'm sorry.

96
00:06:26,999 --> 00:06:29,777
Tomorrow is Nuo Nuo's parents' death anniversary,

97
00:06:29,777 --> 00:06:32,334
so we might be a bit busy.

98
00:06:32,334 --> 00:06:35,592
However, we can still prepare your meals.

99
00:06:41,209 --> 00:06:42,999
By the way, Mr. Bai,

100
00:06:42,999 --> 00:06:45,883
you aren't going to sleep yet, right?

101
00:06:47,711 --> 00:06:49,467
Is there anything you need?

102
00:07:08,276 --> 00:07:10,175
What are you doing here?

103
00:07:10,999 --> 00:07:13,209
Nothing, I just...

104
00:07:13,209 --> 00:07:15,925
I want to experience Kinmen's nightlife.

105
00:07:19,918 --> 00:07:21,799
The door.

106
00:07:34,792 --> 00:07:40,759
Well, Grandma told me to watch the deer at night,

107
00:07:42,250 --> 00:07:44,718
so I came to take a look.

108
00:07:54,042 --> 00:07:57,042
On a day like this,

109
00:07:57,042 --> 00:07:59,676
it's better to have someone with you.

110
00:08:02,050 --> 00:08:06,584
I spend a day like this alone every year.

111
00:08:06,584 --> 00:08:08,300
I'm used to it.

112
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:27,626
It's called Little Bambi.

113
00:08:27,626 --> 00:08:29,751
Its parents aren't around anymore either.

114
00:08:29,751 --> 00:08:32,799
I come to see it every year around this time.

115
00:08:33,999 --> 00:08:36,351
You can use this to feed it.

116
00:08:36,351 --> 00:08:37,553
However, it depends on its mood.

117
00:08:37,553 --> 00:08:39,342
It might not eat.

118
00:08:42,535 --> 00:08:43,626
Little Bambi.

119
00:08:43,626 --> 00:08:44,999
Bambi.

120
00:08:44,999 --> 00:08:46,925
Little Bambi, over here.

121
00:08:53,467 --> 00:08:56,134
You need to attract its attention.

122
00:09:01,834 --> 00:09:03,799
There you go.

123
00:09:06,209 --> 00:09:09,134
Feed it slowly.

124
00:09:12,792 --> 00:09:14,592
Keep going.

125
00:09:16,250 --> 00:09:18,799
You can pet it. It doesn't bite.

126
00:09:27,276 --> 00:09:30,125
Was it always this chubby?

127
00:09:30,125 --> 00:09:32,612
That's called well-fed.

128
00:09:32,612 --> 00:09:34,799
Looks like it's in a good mood.

129
00:09:37,042 --> 00:09:38,799
Little Bambi.

130
00:10:16,761 --> 00:10:20,799
The dishes at a fancy restaurant have to look brand new.

131
00:10:22,434 --> 00:10:25,676
I'm washing them cleaner than a dishwasher.

132
00:10:29,050 --> 00:10:33,452
That day, Yin Mo came to celebrate your birthday.

133
00:10:33,452 --> 00:10:35,125
You guys...

134
00:10:35,125 --> 00:10:37,792
Carrying trays needs some skills.

135
00:10:37,792 --> 00:10:39,876
I have to carry 30 plates at once.

136
00:10:39,876 --> 00:10:42,799
I could join a circus with this skill.

137
00:10:46,209 --> 00:10:49,527
The money Yin Mo gave you to buy two houses

138
00:10:49,527 --> 00:10:52,175
should've lasted you both a lifetime.

139
00:10:52,867 --> 00:10:56,217
How did he blow it all?

140
00:11:00,627 --> 00:11:03,085
We failed in business.

141
00:11:03,085 --> 00:11:05,485
He wanted me to ask Yin Mo for more money,

142
00:11:05,485 --> 00:11:07,175
but I refused.

143
00:11:08,428 --> 00:11:11,883
I wasn't useful to him anymore, so he left me.

144
00:11:14,494 --> 00:11:16,967
However, I'm fine now.

145
00:11:17,900 --> 00:11:21,925
At least I can support myself.

146
00:11:23,452 --> 00:11:24,933
Sorry.

147
00:11:24,933 --> 00:11:27,009
I still have work to do.

148
00:11:42,867 --> 00:11:44,900
Yu Mei, thank you.

149
00:11:44,900 --> 00:11:46,761
Bye.

150
00:11:46,761 --> 00:11:48,375
Manager, I'm leaving now.

151
00:11:48,375 --> 00:11:50,459
Yu Mei, wait.

152
00:11:50,459 --> 00:11:51,759
Yu Mei, I just wanted to let you know.

153
00:11:51,759 --> 00:11:54,799
I'm raising your salary to 40,000 starting next month.

154
00:11:55,561 --> 00:11:57,976
A whole 10,000 more?

155
00:11:57,976 --> 00:11:59,518
Yes, so keep up the good work.

156
00:11:59,518 --> 00:12:01,384
Keep doing your best.

157
00:12:03,627 --> 00:12:06,419
Is it because of that lady who came today

158
00:12:06,419 --> 00:12:08,799
that you're paying me more?

159
00:12:11,209 --> 00:12:12,842
Yes.

160
00:12:13,702 --> 00:12:17,794
Please give the money back to her.

161
00:12:17,794 --> 00:12:20,643
You've got to be kidding me.

162
00:12:20,643 --> 00:12:23,676
Are you turning down money that has been handed to you?

163
00:12:28,786 --> 00:12:31,009
I'm not worth that amount.

164
00:12:32,083 --> 00:12:33,083
That's it.

165
00:12:33,083 --> 00:12:35,476
Just write the info down.

166
00:12:35,476 --> 00:12:38,592
- That's it.
- All right. I'll give it a shot.

167
00:12:39,999 --> 00:12:42,660
Shun Hua, why are you suddenly hiring?

168
00:12:42,660 --> 00:12:45,786
You're even learning to manage a fan page.

169
00:12:45,786 --> 00:12:48,259
Isn't Zhi Ting the one who usually handles that?

170
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:52,577
Well, she has worked hard for so many years.

171
00:12:52,577 --> 00:12:54,083
I need to learn to be independent, too.

172
00:12:54,083 --> 00:12:55,883
What do you mean?

173
00:12:58,434 --> 00:13:00,300
It's nothing.

174
00:13:01,042 --> 00:13:03,125
She suddenly told me

175
00:13:03,125 --> 00:13:07,202
that she wants to withdraw her investment in the restaurant.

176
00:13:07,202 --> 00:13:09,592
Is she looking to invest in something else?

177
00:13:10,417 --> 00:13:11,662
Mr. Bai, look.

178
00:13:11,662 --> 00:13:15,799
Nowadays, a lot of celebrities are investing.

179
00:13:17,518 --> 00:13:19,175
I know.

180
00:13:20,535 --> 00:13:22,452
I've actually looked into it.

181
00:13:22,452 --> 00:13:24,999
When it comes to side businesses for celebrities,

182
00:13:24,999 --> 00:13:27,999
most of them have boutiques, spas,

183
00:13:27,999 --> 00:13:30,711
and all sorts of other ventures.

184
00:13:30,711 --> 00:13:35,092
However, the most profitable one is still catering.

185
00:13:36,327 --> 00:13:37,951
Am I going from being a guest of the guesthouse

186
00:13:37,951 --> 00:13:40,226
to being your investor?

187
00:13:40,226 --> 00:13:42,452
Investor?

188
00:13:42,452 --> 00:13:45,720
That's just a term.

189
00:13:45,720 --> 00:13:51,009
You can think of it as opening up another path in life.

190
00:13:51,009 --> 00:13:52,125
That's a better fit.

191
00:13:52,125 --> 00:13:54,342
Are you opening a new branch?

192
00:13:57,494 --> 00:13:59,560
I asked her the same thing,

193
00:13:59,560 --> 00:14:01,467
but she told me

194
00:14:02,209 --> 00:14:03,867
she wants to leave Kinmen.

195
00:14:03,867 --> 00:14:05,645
I was going to ask more,

196
00:14:05,645 --> 00:14:07,561
but seeing how awkward and uneasy she looked,

197
00:14:07,561 --> 00:14:10,592
I didn't want to push her.

198
00:14:12,217 --> 00:14:14,799
Could it be that she wants to cut ties with you?

199
00:14:17,502 --> 00:14:19,720
Does it really have to be like that?

200
00:14:19,720 --> 00:14:20,918
No, that's not what I meant.

201
00:14:20,918 --> 00:14:21,934
Forget I said anything.

202
00:14:21,934 --> 00:14:23,083
No, I wasn't talking about you.

203
00:14:23,083 --> 00:14:25,209
I was talking about Zhi Ting.

204
00:14:25,209 --> 00:14:28,009
Not opening a branch? Then why did you come to me?

205
00:14:34,900 --> 00:14:38,300
I want to...

206
00:14:39,167 --> 00:14:41,709
I want to leave Shun Hua.

207
00:14:41,709 --> 00:14:43,959
I guess she might have found someone new.

208
00:14:43,959 --> 00:14:45,744
However, I can't blame her.

209
00:14:45,744 --> 00:14:47,035
We've been broken up for a while now

210
00:14:47,035 --> 00:14:49,542
and I kept telling her that she could find someone else.

211
00:14:49,542 --> 00:14:50,876
But you know me, Chen Da Wu.

212
00:14:50,876 --> 00:14:53,584
I was just saying it, but I didn't actually mean it.

213
00:14:53,584 --> 00:14:55,999
Well, that's just your guess.

214
00:14:55,999 --> 00:14:59,375
I know the last time you fought was because of the bill.

215
00:14:59,375 --> 00:15:00,999
But you also mentioned a lot of other things

216
00:15:00,999 --> 00:15:02,735
like your daily habits not matching

217
00:15:02,735 --> 00:15:04,209
and personality differences.

218
00:15:04,209 --> 00:15:06,351
Maybe she just wanted...

219
00:15:06,351 --> 00:15:08,417
To scare me?

220
00:15:08,417 --> 00:15:09,999
To give me a warning?

221
00:15:09,999 --> 00:15:11,842
It could be.

222
00:15:16,393 --> 00:15:19,652
I'm afraid that if I take back the investment,

223
00:15:19,652 --> 00:15:22,901
he won't be able to manage it.

224
00:15:22,901 --> 00:15:27,351
I don't know who else to ask for help, so...

225
00:15:27,351 --> 00:15:31,217
Maybe you're the only one who can help me.

226
00:15:33,900 --> 00:15:39,592
Even though we broke up, we were together for so long.

227
00:15:40,735 --> 00:15:43,799
I still want him to live a good life.

228
00:15:48,744 --> 00:15:50,467
I get it now.

229
00:15:51,459 --> 00:15:55,634
So, you came to me for investment to ease your guilt?

230
00:15:56,500 --> 00:15:58,676
I know you're worried about him.

231
00:16:00,900 --> 00:16:03,110
However, have you ever thought

232
00:16:03,110 --> 00:16:07,467
that maybe leaving him might make him better off?

233
00:16:14,368 --> 00:16:18,009
After all, nobody will stop living because they're missing someone.

234
00:16:29,999 --> 00:16:31,800
Ms. Ye Zhi Ting.

235
00:16:32,577 --> 00:16:35,654
Welcome to today's ribbon-cutting ceremony.

236
00:16:35,654 --> 00:16:37,695
This new bathroom door

237
00:16:37,695 --> 00:16:39,428
guarantees you won't get locked inside

238
00:16:39,428 --> 00:16:43,259
and it will give you full privacy when using the bathroom.

239
00:16:44,042 --> 00:16:45,327
And the new laundry basket.

240
00:16:45,327 --> 00:16:46,351
From now on, when I get home,

241
00:16:46,351 --> 00:16:49,384
I'll toss my dirty clothes and smelly socks into it.

242
00:16:50,461 --> 00:16:52,042
And with the new mouthwash,

243
00:16:52,042 --> 00:16:53,900
I can rinse right after eating garlic

244
00:16:53,900 --> 00:16:56,676
and always have fresh breath.

245
00:17:00,434 --> 00:17:02,509
I have...

246
00:17:05,867 --> 00:17:07,925
someone new.

247
00:18:57,417 --> 00:18:59,342
Hey, Da Wu. What's up?

248
00:18:59,342 --> 00:19:01,428
Hey, Hai Nuo. Is my dad with you?

249
00:19:01,428 --> 00:19:02,720
He isn't here yet.

250
00:19:02,720 --> 00:19:04,999
He disappeared this morning.

251
00:19:04,999 --> 00:19:06,285
Disappeared?

252
00:19:06,285 --> 00:19:08,202
Yes, but it's probably nothing serious.

253
00:19:08,202 --> 00:19:10,151
I'll go look for him.

254
00:19:10,151 --> 00:19:12,520
He never leaves without his phone.

255
00:19:12,520 --> 00:19:14,711
Don't worry, Mom. Dad only goes to a few places.

256
00:19:14,711 --> 00:19:17,925
Wait at home and let me know when he gets back.

257
00:19:22,801 --> 00:19:24,834
Grandma.

258
00:19:24,834 --> 00:19:26,285
Da Wu said he couldn't find his dad.

259
00:19:26,285 --> 00:19:28,800
I'll go look for him. I'll be right back.

260
00:19:51,494 --> 00:19:53,217
Dad.

261
00:19:54,250 --> 00:19:56,669
Ma'am, have you seen the Village Chief?

262
00:19:56,669 --> 00:19:59,459
- No, I haven't.
- Okay, thank you.

263
00:19:59,459 --> 00:20:02,118
- Dad!
- Ma'am, did you see Mr. Fu Shou today?

264
00:20:02,118 --> 00:20:03,134
No, I didn't.

265
00:20:03,134 --> 00:20:04,799
Okay, thank you.

266
00:20:05,485 --> 00:20:07,561
Ma'am, has Mr. Fu Shou been here today?

267
00:20:07,561 --> 00:20:09,594
No, he hasn't.

268
00:20:09,594 --> 00:20:11,586
